v 3
d reshapehelper: diagnose the dataset and suggest (never run) the likely reshape command
d
d A dry-run advisor for Stata's hardest data-management command.
d reshapehelper never reshapes your data. It scans variable names for
d wide patterns (numeric suffixes, string suffixes, @ mid-name stubs,
d doubly-wide double indices), finds candidate i and j variables
d (honoring xtset/tsset and svyset declarations), decides the likely
d direction, composes the reshape command, and TESTS it on a small
d sample inside preserve/restore, iterating on reshape's own errors
d (string j, spaces in j, duplicates within i-j, non-constant
d variables) until the suggestion runs or the blocker is diagnosed.
d Output: an ASCII before/after diagram of what the suggestion would
d do, the suggested syntax with its dry-run verdict (also stored in
d r(cmd) and $reshapehelper_cmd, written unwrapped to a viewable SMCL
d file, and offered as a click-to-run link), or - when it cannot
d discern the design - a numbered checklist of what to fix or specify
d before running reshapehelper again. Flags transpose jobs that are
d really xpose/sxpose problems.
d
d Requires: Stata 16.0 or newer
d
d Author: Eric A. Booth, Sr Researcher, Texas 2036
d Support: eric.a.booth@gmail.com
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260715
d
f reshapehelper.ado
f reshapehelper.sthlp
f example_reshapehelper.do
